        <h2 id="Navigation" class="col-12 order-first">Navigation</h2>
        <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-7 col-lg-7 col-xl-7" style="float:left;">
            <p>
                ESPN website’s menu bar is slim and unobtrusive, but it offers a comprehensive drop down menu. 
                It has the standard home button logo, but isn’t located at the absolute top, which sets it apart and 
                looks intentional. It is also different that it doesn’t offer any obvious links to information 
                about ESPN itself, but that could be on a parent site or network site. The sight navigation does 
                seem logical in it’s organization by putting easily understood links to what I assume are its 
                highest areas of traffic. The two things that are odd as I navigate the sight are that the login 
                isn’t included in the navigation bar and when the screen is at a tablet size accessing the menu 
                causes the rest of the screen to go black.</br>
                <a href="#top">top</a>
            </p>
        </div>
