        <h2 id="Design" class="col-12 order-first">Design</h2>
        <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-7 col-lg-7 col-xl-7 order-last">
            <p>
                ESPN’s homepage has several different types of media. It has no advertisements. The page is very 
                full of content, but I think that is on purpose. It’s layout is like a news site, which is appropriate 
                because it is a news site, just dedicated to sports. The content scales no matter what the size and I 
                would say it’s appropriate for the site.They only problem I had was it seems like there’s a missing 
                gap in their media queries because with Firefox I was able to resize the window and hit an area that 
                seems to make much of the CSS ineffective.</br>
                <a href="#top">top</a>
            </p>
        </div>
