    <div class="row pad stripe1">
        <h2 id="Content" class="col-12 order-first">Content</h2>
        <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-7 col-lg-7 col-xl-7">
            <p>
                ESPN’s website does seem fresh and has to be fresh. Part of its core function as a sports news outlet demands 
                that the site have up to date scores and new articles every day. I don’t know if there is a particular synergy 
                in the design and content, but the designs and colors are easy on the eye and brink the eye to where they want 
                their consumers to look. I think this website’s content fulfills the function of giving the user recent sports 
                news. On side note this website seems to be geared towards american sports news, but for all I know they have 
                an adaptive design that changes the sports highlighted depending on incoming IP address.</br>
                <a href="#top">top</a>
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-5 col-lg-5 col-xl-5 order-last">
