            <p>
                The ESPN website has a couple changes I would make. They are:
                <ul>
                    <li>Look into the media query or browser normalizing CSS and see what is causing the odd spot in screen size change.</li>
                    <li>Try adding some interactive parts of the homepage that don’t involve navigating.Try something like expanding 
                        the content focused upon, or moving the content to a bigger area where it can be seen with greater detail.</li>
                    <li>If the having the user sign up and login is important to their site purpose then maybe think about moving 
                        those to the menu bar.</li>
                </ul>
                <a href="#top">top</a>
            </p>
